    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CPU measurements enable command and statistics display in telnet server\n\n### Summary\nThe `measurcmd_cpustats` function in the telnet server had two major issues:\n1. The \"enable\" command was not actually enabling CPU measurements\n2. When called without parameters, it only showed the measurement state instead of displaying actual CPU statistics\n\nThis fix addresses both issues by properly implementing the enable command and making the function display actual CPU statistics when no valid command is provided.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_measurements.c`: \n  - Added missing `#include \"common/utils/time_meas.h\"` header\n  - Fixed the \"enable\" command to actually call `cpumeas(CPUMEAS_ENABLE)`\n  - Enhanced default behavior to display actual CPU statistics when no command is provided\n  - Improved resource management with proper null checks\n  - Made implementation consistent with `measurcmd_show` function patterns\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, when using the telnet server:\n1. Running `measur cpustats enable` would not actually enable CPU measurements\n2. Running `measur cpustats` would only show \"Cpu measurements state: disabled\" instead of actual statistics\n\nAfter this fix:\n1. Running `measur cpustats enable` properly enables CPU measurements\n2. Running `measur cpustats` displays actual CPU statistics from all registered measurement groups\n\n"
}